ere as well company officials planned to open the first such stores in new york minnesota california and virginia the barnes  noble restaurants are expected to include a waitstaff and a full menu for breakfast lunch and dinner community involvementedit barnes  noble hires community business development managers to engage in community outreach these managers responsibilities include organizing instore events such as author appearances childrens storytimes and book groups community business development managers also work closely with local schools and groups to promote literacy and the arts for example barnes  noble sponsors a childrens summer reading program that promotes literacy and puts over  million books into the hands of the children each year barnes  noble also hosts bookfairs which raise funds for schools and libraries and an annual holiday book drive to collect books for disadvantaged children barnes  noble stores collected and donated nearly  million books to more than  local charities across the country that provide services to disadvantaged children during the  holiday book drive to promote nationwide literacy among st to th graders and encourage more reading during the summer barnes  noble has implemented a summer challenge if children read eight books and write about their reading barnes  noble will give the reader a free book barnes  noble nookedit see also barnes  noble nook barnes  noble nook styled nook is a suite of ebook readers developed by the company based on the android platform the first device was announced in the united states on october   and was released november   for  on june   barnes  noble reduced the nooks price to  as well as launched a new wifionly model for  and released a nook colored touch screen for  the nook competes with the amazon kindle kobo ereader and other ereader offerings and color tablets used sometimes as readers such as apples ibooks for ios devices various nook models feature a inch inch or larger touchscreen versi